-- Finans of Turkey Signs Gets $50 Million IFC Loan for Energy Efficiency
-- Mark Bentley
-- 2010-06-22T09:02:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/finans-of-turkey-signs-gets-50-million-ifc-loan-for-energy-efficiency.html

          
          
             Finans Finansal Kiralama AS, a
Turkish leasing company, got a loan of $50 million from the
International Finance Corporation to finance projects to
encourage energy efficiency and sustainability, according to a
filing with the Istanbul Stock Exchange today.  
          
          


  


        